This paper focuses on entity linking, which is a task commonly studied in the information retrieval (IR) and natural language processing (NLP) communities. Therefore, cs.IR and cs.CL are the most likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes the use of graph-based methods and centrality measures, which are common techniques in machine learning and artificial intelligence (AI) research (cs.AI). The experiments are conducted on different datasets, which suggests a focus on generalizability and performance evaluation, common themes in machine learning and data mining (cs.LG). Finally, the paper deals with constructing and analyzing graphs, which is a topic in database systems (cs.DB).
